OP-1 checked evidence discharges the subtracted-index and checked-
division bounds this row used to pin on. The surviving obligation is
guard-dependent: `i < 2` emitted inside the true branch of
`iteM (ltNat i 2 …)` under only `h_gen_bounds_ : i < 4` — the branch
guard is not available as evidence at the obligation site, so the
bound is unprovable in place. Guarded evidence-less access is Slice
OP-2's surface (the runtime-checked accessor makes the branch
error-faithful). True differential tests may not rely on `sorry`.
